  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-03-07",
    "date": "2007-03-16T17:52:07Z",
    "text": "Homeland Security Transparency Act of 2007 - Amends the Homeland Security Act of 2002 to direct the Secretary of Homeland Security to: (1) require homeland security grant recipients to submit quarterly reports describing the nature and amount of each expenditure made using grant funds; and (2) publish such information and make it publicly available on the Department of Homeland Security's (DHS) Internet website."
